                </div>
                
                <div>
                    <a name="bookmark266">R13-6-704. Requirements of a Firearms-safety Instructor </a>
                </div>
                <div>A firearms-safety instructor shall:</div>
                <ol id="l307">
                    <li>
                        <div>Conduct only firearms-safety training programs that are established by the Department;</div>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <div>Conduct Department-established firearms-safety training programs only in this state;</div>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <div>Maintain for five years the following firearms-safety training records regarding each individual to whom training is provided:</div>
                        <ol id="l308">
                            <li>
                                <div>Name and age of the individual at the time training started;</div>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <div>Date and number of hours of each training session;</div>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <div>Location of each training session;</div>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <div>Name of the security guard agency or firearms safety training organization sponsoring the training session;</div>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <div>Title and Department-assigned number of the training program; and</div>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <div>Whether the individual passed, failed, or withdrew from the training program; and</div>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <div>Make the firearms-safety training records referenced in subsection (3) available for inspection upon request by the Department.</div>
                    </li>
